<!-- START OF EVENTS SECTION -->
<section id="events" class="events-container">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Race Calendar</h2>
        <p>Here are some of our partner events around the country in the lead up to the Festival which you may want to incorporate into your training schedule. </p>

        <div class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
                <time datetime="2019-04-28" class="icon">
                    <em>Sunday</em>
                    <strong>April</strong>
                    <span>28</span>
                </time>
            </div>
            <div class="event-info">
                <h3>Wexford Half Marathon or 10km</h3>
                <p>
                    The Wexford Half Marathon has proven itself over the years as Ireland’s record breaking course.
                    In 2012 a Guinness world record was broken in retro running! Individually people have consistently gotten PB’s.
                    Our Half marathon also has pacers catering for 1.30 / 1.45 / 2hrs to help you achieve your target time.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Last year 1,900 people enjoyed the scenic and fast course around Wexford town.
                    Wexford has proven itself a must do race for quality, friendliness and atmosphere.
                    Parking is easy and the course has plenty of variety starting in the town and taking you around surrounding countryside.
                    This year there'll be a new medal with a subtle bottle opener awaiting you at the very atmospheric finish line. Finish on a high note in Wexford!
                </p>
                <p>Enter online at <a href="http://rundublin.com/race/advert-wexford-half-marathon-10km-23rd-april/" target="_blank">http://rundublin.com/race/advert-wexford-half-marathon-10km-23rd-april/</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
                <time datetime="2019-06-15" class="icon">
                    <em>Saturday</em>
                    <strong>June</strong>
                    <span>15</span>
                </time>
            </div>
            <div class="event-info">
                <h3>Half on the Head</h3>
                <p>
                    The Half on the Head follows a wonderfully scenic course from Ballyheigue Village right around Kerryhead (one of the closest places to the USA).
                </p>
                <p>
                    The 13.2 mile run takes you along one of the hidden gems of the Wild Atlantic Way by the Shannon Estuary with views accross the river mouth to the coast of Clare.
                    Glancing back you will see the rugged Kerry coastline stretching to the town of Ballybunion. You might even catch a glimpse of the fabled Cliffs of Dooneen.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Upon rounding the point of Kerryhead you will experience the magnificent panorama of Tralee Bay with Mount Brandon and the Maherees as a backdrop.
                    Further along you have stunning views of the coastline stretching from Ballyheigue beach to Banna and Fenit with Blennerville Windmill in the distance.
                </p>
                <p>A 10k run also takes place on the day. Entry costs €25 – €40.</p>
                <p>
                    Enter online at <a href="http://halfonthehead.com/" target="_blank">http://halfonthehead.com/</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
                <time datetime="2019-07-06" class="icon">
                    <em>Saturday</em>
                    <strong>July</strong>
                    <span>6</span>
                </time>
            </div>
            <div class="event-info">
                <h3>Clontarf Half Marathon or 5 Mile</h3>
                <p>
                    Ireland’s summer race takes place on Ireland’s flattest course….
                    Clontarf Half & 5 mile is not only Ireland’s flattest race but it is also one of the most popular. Clontarf has sold out 10 times in a row!
                    3,000 people to hang out with. That along with PB potential and the great atmosphere you come to expect.
                </p>
                <p>
                    There's a new bespoke medal this year that will look great around your neck!
                    Do not miss out, secure your place now as places are limited and it will sell out.
                    Pacers available for the Half Marathon: 1hr30, 1hr40, 1hr45, 1hr50, and 2hours.
                </p>
                <p>Enter online at <a href="http://rundublin.com/race/clontarf/" target="_blank">http://rundublin.com/race/clontarf/</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
                <time datetime="2019-07-20" class="icon">
                    <em>Saturday</em>
                    <strong>July</strong>
                    <span>20</span>
                </time>
            </div>
            <div class="event-info">
                <h3>Run Killarney Half Marathon and 10k race</h3>
                <p>
                    The Run Killarney event is probably one of the most scenic road races in world (after the Dingle Running Festival of course!).
                    With a 10K and half marathon and similar courses to Dingle, it would make a great part of your training plan towards the Dingle Festival.
                </p>
                <p>Enter online at <a href="https://runkillarney.com/" target="_blank">https://runkillarney.com/</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
                <time datetime="2019-08-11" class="icon">
                    <em>Sunday</em>
                    <strong>August</strong>
                    <span>11</span>
                </time>
            </div>
            <div class="event-info">
                <h3>Rock ‘n’ Roll Dublin</h3>
                <p>
                    Rock ‘n’ Roll Dublin is the most fun you’ll ever have running. 
                    Experience live music along the course and journey along the River Liffey past Christ Church Cathedral and the famous Guinness Brewery. 
                    Afterwards enjoy the headline act at the finish festival concert.
                </p>
                <p>The weekend of running includes a 5k on Saturday where you can pick up your first bit of race bling. 
                Sunday’s events include a 10k and Family Fun Event as well as the feature event, the Half Marathon.</p>
                <p>Enter online at <a href="https://www.runrocknroll.com/en/events/dublin" target="_blank">https://www.runrocknroll.com/en/events/dublin</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
                <time datetime="2019-09-08" class="icon">
                    <em>Sunday</em>
                    <strong>September</strong>
                    <span>8</span>
                </time>
            </div>
            <div class="event-info">
                <h3>Derryheen Harvest Run, Butlersbridge, Co. Cavan</h3>
                <p>
                    Now in its 5th year, this event is organised by Derryheen Parish Church in aid of its Restoration Fund and St Christopher’s Hospice, Cavan.
                </p>
                <p>
                    10K and 5K starting at 12 noon, suitable for walkers and runners.
                    NEW: 20K event starting at 11AM. Suitable for those training for marathon.
                </p>
                <p>
                    There are 2 substantial hills in the 10k event in the final 5k. The 1st 5k is flat. There are 3 water stations on the 10K route at 3, 5.9 and 7.4KM.
                    There are 1 KM markers so contestants can keep track of their progress and a timing clock at the finish line.
                    There is beautiful countryside on quiet roads on a loop of Lough Inchin on the boundaries of Farnham Estate. The event begins and ends at Derryheen Church.
                </p>
                <p>Registration is at the event from 10.45AM. Entry fees are €10 per adult and €20 per family.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

    </div>
</section>
